cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.GT 

The paper deals with reinforcement learning applied to multi-agent systems, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper proposes algorithms for joint objective optimization, which is a common problem in multi-agent systems, and uses fairness in cellular base-station scheduling as an example to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithms.
